main event: A civilian observer in Finlayson, Minnesota reported seeing a white, oval-shaped object about three times the size of the full moon on October 7, 1966.
interesting points: The object was pulsating and at times had multi-colored lights at the bottom.
The object was observed for about 20 minutes, during which time it remained stationary in the sky.
The observer went to get another witness, and when they returned, the object was gone.
The weather conditions were clear and quiet, with no moon.
The air force received calls from other observers in the area, and a newspaper editor also reported seeing a streak of light in the southwest sky around the same time.
sighted object: a white, oval-shaped object about three times the size of the full moon
